    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="duk.00447.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Burlington, Vt.</name>
                    <date when="1890-05-03">May 3&#8212;<add rend="insertion" place="infralinear"
                                ><handShift new="#h2"/>'90</add><handShift new="#h1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Bro Walt,</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>Han<ptr target="n0285"/> is gaining yet of course impatient&#8212;</p>

            <p>Any word or notice of you she studies closely&#8212;</p>

            <p>Hard times with me for money&#8212;</p>

            <p>I sent a painting to New York&#8212;to Aquila Rich<ptr target="n5000"/>, 84 William St&#8212;reported
                safe&#8212;and carefully <choice>
                    <sic>hang</sic>
                    <corr>hung</corr>
                </choice> up&#8212;&#8212;</p>

            <p>I am wearing a <choice>
                    <sic>batterd</sic>
                    <corr>battered</corr>
                </choice> old hat&#8212;Shame on Burlington Vermont&#8212;&#8212;<choice>
                    <sic>allmost</sic>
                    <corr>almost</corr>
                </choice> begging for victuals&#8212;or provisions at times&#8212;Yet hope to
                surpass my troubles yet.</p>

            <closer>
                <signed>Charlie</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
